The Logic behind this question where are series of tanks that holder rain water.
Each tank bottom is at a different height, so each tank capacity depends on the smallest wall that is on the leftside or right side of the tank.
We have to check how much water each tank can hold based on it's smallest adjacent wall and should return the sum of water that all th tanks can hold.

Algorithm:

1. Initialize the left pointer , right pointer , leftMax(highest wall from left), rightMax(max wall height from right side), and water(holdes sum of all the water)
2. While left < right , which if left wall is smaller or right side wall is smaller(which ever side is smaller will control the water.
3. Now  check if current hight is >= previous leftMax or rightMax 
    if true then this will become the next leftMax or rightMax (as this is the biggest wall seen until now) .
    else calculate water leftMax or rightMax - current height at left or right and respective pointer increments.
4. Return water.


Class solution{
  public int rainWater(int[] height)
  {
  int left =0, right = height.length - 1;
  int leftMax = 0, rightMax = 0, water = 0;

  while(left < right)
  {

    if(height[left] < height[right])
    {
      if(height[left] >= leftMax) leftMax = height[left];
      else water += leftMax - height[left];

      left++;
    }
    else
    {
    if(height[right] >= rightMax) rightMax = height[right];
    else water += rightMax - height[right];

    right--;
    }
  }

  return water;
  }
  }
  
